<subSubSection pageId="229" pageNumber="230" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="229.[151,760,391,458]" box="[151,307,431,458]" pageId="229" pageNumber="230">
<figureCitation box="[151,307,431,458]" captionStart="FIGURES 384–387" captionStartId="230.[151,269,929,953]" captionTargetBox="[193,1387,216,867]" captionTargetId="figure-216@230.[151,1436,197,902]" captionTargetPageId="230" captionText="FIGURES 384–387. Potamyia assamana Oláh &amp; Schefter, new species, holotype, male. 384 — genitalia, lateral; 385 — genitalia, dorsal; 386 — gonocoxite, ventral; 387 — phallus, lateral." pageId="229" pageNumber="230">
Fig. 384 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[248,263,431,457]" pageId="229" pageNumber="230">–</emphasis>
387
</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="229.[151,1437,512,1938]" pageId="229" pageNumber="230">
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Malicky" authorityName="Malicky" box="[458,682,512,538]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Potamyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="229" pageNumber="230" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="daphne">
<emphasis box="[458,574,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="229" pageNumber="230">P. daphne</emphasis>
Malicky
</taxonomicName>
described from 
<collectingRegion box="[878,959,512,538]" country="India" name="Kerala" pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Kerala</collectingRegion>
, and later recorded from 
<collectingRegion box="[1264,1384,512,538]" country="India" name="Karnataka" pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Karnataka</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[151,289,552,578]" country="India" name="Tamil Nadu" pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Tamil Nadu</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Olah, J." box="[305,514,552,578]" pageId="229" pageNumber="230" pagination="37 - 38" refId="ref111356" refString="Olah, J. (2006 a) Sexual dimorphism helps deep diving in Potamyia johansoni n. sp. (Trichoptera: Hydropsychidae). Braueria, 33, 37 - 38." type="journal article" year="2006">
Oláh 
<emphasis box="[372,430,552,577]" italics="true" pageId="229" pageNumber="230">et al.</emphasis>
2006a
</bibRefCitation>
). It differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[708,822,552,577]" class="Insecta" family="Hydropsychidae" genus="Potamyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="229" pageNumber="230" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="daphne">
<emphasis box="[708,822,552,577]" italics="true" pageId="229" pageNumber="230">P. daphne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the straight, not rounded anterior margins of segment IX; longer segment X; U-shaped, dorsal interlobular gap; phallotheca with straight, not undulating dorsum; and very large sub-apical ventral lobes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="229.[151,1437,512,1938]" pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Male. Body and wings light brown, with brown pubescence. Forewing membrane without maculation. Antennae less than twice as long as forewings. Abdominal segment V with minute, pointed, lobes. Spur formula 144. Protibiae with small spur. Pretarsal claws asymmetrical, laterally flanked by setal bundle. Mid- and hind-leg claws asymmetrical.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="229.[151,1437,512,1938]" pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Wings. Forewing crossveins m-cu and cu running closely. Cu2 and A joining before wing margin. Hind wing stem of M plus proximal part of M3+4 almost tangential, running parallel with Cu1. Fork 1 present. Forewing 8.0 mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="229.[151,1437,512,1938]" pageId="229" pageNumber="230">
Male genitalia. Abdominal segment IX fused annularly, short; tergum half as long as sternum (
<figureCitation box="[1319,1424,952,978]" captionStart="FIGURES 384–387" captionStartId="230.[151,269,929,953]" captionTargetBox="[193,1387,216,867]" captionTargetId="figure-216@230.[151,1436,197,902]" captionTargetPageId="230" captionText="FIGURES 384–387. Potamyia assamana Oláh &amp; Schefter, new species, holotype, male. 384 — genitalia, lateral; 385 — genitalia, dorsal; 386 — gonocoxite, ventral; 387 — phallus, lateral." pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Fig. 384</figureCitation>
). Anterior margins of segment IX straight, with posteriorly shifted dorsal section in lateral aspect (
<figureCitation box="[1318,1424,992,1018]" captionStart="FIGURES 384–387" captionStartId="230.[151,269,929,953]" captionTargetBox="[193,1387,216,867]" captionTargetId="figure-216@230.[151,1436,197,902]" captionTargetPageId="230" captionText="FIGURES 384–387. Potamyia assamana Oláh &amp; Schefter, new species, holotype, male. 384 — genitalia, lateral; 385 — genitalia, dorsal; 386 — gonocoxite, ventral; 387 — phallus, lateral." pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Fig. 384</figureCitation>
). Apical lobe on posterolateral margins small, almost absent, located immediately above narrow articulation cavity of gonocoxites (
<figureCitation box="[424,529,1072,1098]" captionStart="FIGURES 384–387" captionStartId="230.[151,269,929,953]" captionTargetBox="[193,1387,216,867]" captionTargetId="figure-216@230.[151,1436,197,902]" captionTargetPageId="230" captionText="FIGURES 384–387. Potamyia assamana Oláh &amp; Schefter, new species, holotype, male. 384 — genitalia, lateral; 385 — genitalia, dorsal; 386 — gonocoxite, ventral; 387 — phallus, lateral." pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Fig. 384</figureCitation>
). Spine row on posterior margins of segment IX almost complete, not intermittent, with short gaps; spine lengths heterogenous; spines on laterocaudal protuberances of dorsum about 2 times longer than spines on posterior margina of segment IX; spines on apical lobes stiff, very densely set (
<figureCitation box="[159,264,1192,1218]" captionStart="FIGURES 384–387" captionStartId="230.[151,269,929,953]" captionTargetBox="[193,1387,216,867]" captionTargetId="figure-216@230.[151,1436,197,902]" captionTargetPageId="230" captionText="FIGURES 384–387. Potamyia assamana Oláh &amp; Schefter, new species, holotype, male. 384 — genitalia, lateral; 385 — genitalia, dorsal; 386 — gonocoxite, ventral; 387 — phallus, lateral." pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Fig. 384</figureCitation>
). Intersegmental step between segments IX and X deep, partly occupied by pair of setose protuberances; appearing as setose laterocaudal lobes. Body of segment X long, with ventrad curving distal half ending in dorsad curving hook in lateral aspect (
<figureCitation box="[687,791,1272,1298]" captionStart="FIGURES 384–387" captionStartId="230.[151,269,929,953]" captionTargetBox="[193,1387,216,867]" captionTargetId="figure-216@230.[151,1436,197,902]" captionTargetPageId="230" captionText="FIGURES 384–387. Potamyia assamana Oláh &amp; Schefter, new species, holotype, male. 384 — genitalia, lateral; 385 — genitalia, dorsal; 386 — gonocoxite, ventral; 387 — phallus, lateral." pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Fig. 384</figureCitation>
); bilobed in dorsal aspect (
<figureCitation box="[1114,1218,1272,1298]" captionStart="FIGURES 384–387" captionStartId="230.[151,269,929,953]" captionTargetBox="[193,1387,216,867]" captionTargetId="figure-216@230.[151,1436,197,902]" captionTargetPageId="230" captionText="FIGURES 384–387. Potamyia assamana Oláh &amp; Schefter, new species, holotype, male. 384 — genitalia, lateral; 385 — genitalia, dorsal; 386 — gonocoxite, ventral; 387 — phallus, lateral." pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Fig. 385</figureCitation>
); ventrum bellied; curving apicoventral spiny hook dominating distal part (
<figureCitation box="[820,925,1312,1338]" captionStart="FIGURES 384–387" captionStartId="230.[151,269,929,953]" captionTargetBox="[193,1387,216,867]" captionTargetId="figure-216@230.[151,1436,197,902]" captionTargetPageId="230" captionText="FIGURES 384–387. Potamyia assamana Oláh &amp; Schefter, new species, holotype, male. 384 — genitalia, lateral; 385 — genitalia, dorsal; 386 — gonocoxite, ventral; 387 — phallus, lateral." pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Fig. 384</figureCitation>
). Smooth mesal lobe reduced; dorsal interlobular gap U-shaped, wide, deep to mid-length of apex (
<figureCitation box="[820,923,1352,1378]" captionStart="FIGURES 384–387" captionStartId="230.[151,269,929,953]" captionTargetBox="[193,1387,216,867]" captionTargetId="figure-216@230.[151,1436,197,902]" captionTargetPageId="230" captionText="FIGURES 384–387. Potamyia assamana Oláh &amp; Schefter, new species, holotype, male. 384 — genitalia, lateral; 385 — genitalia, dorsal; 386 — gonocoxite, ventral; 387 — phallus, lateral." pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Fig. 385</figureCitation>
). Dorsad curving apex of spiny hooks separated by dorsal interlobular gap, forming pair of birdbeak-shaped processes armed with mesad directed, stiff setae; shape highly dependent on observation angle. Setose area present on basal dorsolateral areas of segment X; process between segment IX and X absent. Pair of well-developed protuberances representing laterocaudal lobes present. Transverse and longitudinal sutures invisible. Pair of setose areas (superior or preanal appendages) circular, located at mid-length abouve ventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[855,958,1552,1578]" captionStart="FIGURES 384–387" captionStartId="230.[151,269,929,953]" captionTargetBox="[193,1387,216,867]" captionTargetId="figure-216@230.[151,1436,197,902]" captionTargetPageId="230" captionText="FIGURES 384–387. Potamyia assamana Oláh &amp; Schefter, new species, holotype, male. 384 — genitalia, lateral; 385 — genitalia, dorsal; 386 — gonocoxite, ventral; 387 — phallus, lateral." pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Fig. 384</figureCitation>
), or representing setose dorsal ridge possibly homolog with vestigial dorsal setose lobes. Coxopodites significaltly strongly exceeding apex of segment X; rod-shaped, slightly broadening apicad from mid-length; slightly bending ventrad; uniformly curving mesad in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[519,623,1672,1698]" captionStart="FIGURES 384–387" captionStartId="230.[151,269,929,953]" captionTargetBox="[193,1387,216,867]" captionTargetId="figure-216@230.[151,1436,197,902]" captionTargetPageId="230" captionText="FIGURES 384–387. Potamyia assamana Oláh &amp; Schefter, new species, holotype, male. 384 — genitalia, lateral; 385 — genitalia, dorsal; 386 — gonocoxite, ventral; 387 — phallus, lateral." pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Fig. 386</figureCitation>
). Harpagones short, broad, tapering along their lengths in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[159,266,1712,1738]" captionStart="FIGURES 384–387" captionStartId="230.[151,269,929,953]" captionTargetBox="[193,1387,216,867]" captionTargetId="figure-216@230.[151,1436,197,902]" captionTargetPageId="230" captionText="FIGURES 384–387. Potamyia assamana Oláh &amp; Schefter, new species, holotype, male. 384 — genitalia, lateral; 385 — genitalia, dorsal; 386 — gonocoxite, ventral; 387 — phallus, lateral." pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Fig. 384</figureCitation>
); broader, pointing mesad in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[792,900,1712,1738]" captionStart="FIGURES 384–387" captionStartId="230.[151,269,929,953]" captionTargetBox="[193,1387,216,867]" captionTargetId="figure-216@230.[151,1436,197,902]" captionTargetPageId="230" captionText="FIGURES 384–387. Potamyia assamana Oláh &amp; Schefter, new species, holotype, male. 384 — genitalia, lateral; 385 — genitalia, dorsal; 386 — gonocoxite, ventral; 387 — phallus, lateral." pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Fig. 386</figureCitation>
). Phallotheca with enlarged phallobase (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 384–387" captionStartId="230.[151,269,929,953]" captionTargetBox="[193,1387,216,867]" captionTargetId="figure-216@230.[151,1436,197,902]" captionTargetPageId="230" captionText="FIGURES 384–387. Potamyia assamana Oláh &amp; Schefter, new species, holotype, male. 384 — genitalia, lateral; 385 — genitalia, dorsal; 386 — gonocoxite, ventral; 387 — phallus, lateral." pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Fig. 387</figureCitation>
); straight horizontal shaft with regular straight dorsum; ventral subapical broadening strongly enlarged. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="M. Zang &amp; R.H. Petersen" authorityYear="1989" box="[151,297,1792,1818]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phallaceae" genus="Endophallus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Phallales" pageId="229" pageNumber="9" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Endophallus</taxonomicName>
forming narrow tube at gonopore near bottom of phallobase. Chitinized endothecal process small, circular. Phallotremmal sclerites broad; vertical (
<figureCitation box="[801,903,1832,1858]" captionStart="FIGURES 384–387" captionStartId="230.[151,269,929,953]" captionTargetBox="[193,1387,216,867]" captionTargetId="figure-216@230.[151,1436,197,902]" captionTargetPageId="230" captionText="FIGURES 384–387. Potamyia assamana Oláh &amp; Schefter, new species, holotype, male. 384 — genitalia, lateral; 385 — genitalia, dorsal; 386 — gonocoxite, ventral; 387 — phallus, lateral." pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Fig. 387</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
